The RFC 1101 'DNS Encoding of Network Names and Other Types' doesn't enter
upon a difficult case in 'Names corresponding to organizations' (last
paragraph of section 4.0, page 6).
The issue is : what is to be done when one network is shared between
two or more organizations ?
It might be legal to use a different network-name (at least the domain part
is not the same) for each organization, but there is not in RFC 1101.
Maybe someone has a good answer ...

Francis.Dupont@inria.fr

